    </p>

    <h3>1. Collection of information</h3>
    <p>
      We may collect the following kinds of information when you use the Services:
    </p>
    <h4>Information you provide directly to us</h4>
    <p>
      For certain activities, such as when you register or contact us directly, we may ask you to provide some or all of the following types of information:
      <ul>
        <li>
          Log-in information, including alias, e-mail address, language
        </li>
      </ul>
    </p>
    <p>
      No plain-text passwords will be stored (only hashes) and therefore the personal profile information (including email, country of residence and preferred topics/activities on commonfare.net) will be only accessible by the registered user.
    </p>

    <h3>2. Use of information</h3>
    <p>
      We generally use the information we collect online to:
      <ul>
        <li>Share user-inputted stories and facilitate commentary on such stories;</li>
        <li>Assist users in setting up accounts with commonfare.net</li>
        <li>Communicate support resources with users who have shared stories</li>
        <li>Share anonymized user content reports (e.g., narrative of a story/content, location of a story/content) with third party researchers for research purposes or universities or legislators for advocacy purposes;</li>
